2. The arrangement as defined in claim 1 wherein the capacitive measuring arrangement comprises 
a first lead coupled to the thin conductive member; 
a second lead coupled to the valve body; 
a timing circuit for converting the measured capacitance into a frequency signal; and 
a microprocessor for translating the frequency signal into a signal indicative of the true position of the diaphragm membrane with respect to the valve body.

5. A method of determining the true position of a diaphragm membrane within a diaphragm valve assembly including a valve body having at least a pair of reservoirs controlled by said diaphragm membrane and an actuator for moving said membrane between an open position and a closed position, the method comprising the steps of: 
inserting a thin conductive plate between the diaphragm membrane and the actuator such that said thin conductive plate moves in concert with the membrane; 
measuring the capacitance between the thin conductive plate and the valve body, wherein the capacitance will exhibit a first value when the valve is in the closed position and a second value with the valve is in the open position.
